                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13127002" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2011 22:04:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Transformers can&apos;t be respected in general (many need an index).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the future, perhaps we could use a hybrid approach and detect when an index/searcher is needed and open a new searcher (like my first realtime-get approach used).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13127006" author="ryantxu" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2011 22:04:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;transform documents before adding them to the response&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13127010" author="ryantxu" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2011 22:07:48 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Transformers can&apos;t be respected in general (many need an index).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Right, but many cases should be just fine.  In this patch, I pass in -1 for the docId if it does not know it.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The big thing is that this takes care of field renaming and stuff&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13127024" author="ryantxu" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2011 22:15:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a single patch that now lets you use RealtimeGet from solrj.  without the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2831&quot; title=&quot;BinaryResponseWriter does not read/write IndexableFields correctly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-2831&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-2831&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, solrj fails to read the response even without transformers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this is ready to commit&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13127093" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 13 Oct 2011 23:03:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just took a very quick scan, but it looks good!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;+    server.commit();  // necessary???&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently necessary because the transaction log isn&apos;t enabled by default on the example schema.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
